{"id":244,"parent_id":240,"book_id":1,"content_id":1,"language_id":1,"display_order":244,"title":"Ruth 4","subtitle":"","short_title":"Ruth","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4","content":[["div",[".titleNumber","Chapter 4"],[".studySummary",["i","The nearest relative declines, and Boaz takes Ruth to wife—Ruth bears Obed, through whom came David the king."]]],[".bodyBlock",["div",{"id":"1","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.1","order":"02.09.004.20536"},["b","1"],"Then went Boaz up to the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_1a"},"gate"],", and sat him down there: and, behold, the",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_1b"},"kinsman"],"of whom Boaz spake came by; unto whom he said,",["sup","c"],["a",{"href":"fn_1c"},"Ho, such a one"],"! turn aside, sit down here. And he turned aside, and sat down."],["div",{"id":"2","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.2","order":"02.09.004.20537"},["b","2"],"And he took ten men of the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_2a"},"elders"],"of the city, and said, Sit ye down here. And they sat down."],["div",{"id":"3","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.3","order":"02.09.004.20538"},["b","3"],"And he said unto the kinsman, Naomi, that is come again out of the country of Moab, selleth a parcel of land, which",["i","was"],"our brother Elimelech’s:"],["div",{"id":"4","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.4","order":"02.09.004.20539"},["b","4"],"And I thought to advertise thee, saying,",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_4a"},"Buy"],["i","it"],"before the inhabitants, and before the elders of my people. If thou wilt",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_4b"},"redeem"],["i","it,"],"redeem",["i","it:"],"but if thou wilt not redeem",["i","it, then"],"tell me, that I may know: for",["i","there is"],"none to redeem",["i","it"],"beside thee; and I",["i","am"],"after thee. And he said, I will redeem",["i","it."]],["div",{"id":"5","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.5","order":"02.09.004.20540"},["b","5"],"Then said Boaz, What day thou buyest the field of the hand of Naomi, thou must buy",["i","it"],"also of Ruth the Moabitess, the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_5a"},"wife"],"of the dead, to raise up the",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_5b"},"name"],"of the dead upon his inheritance."],["div",{"id":"6","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.6","order":"02.09.004.20541"},["b","6"],"¶And the kinsman said, I cannot",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_6a"},"redeem"],["i","it"],"for myself, lest I",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_6b"},"mar"],"mine own inheritance: redeem thou my right to thyself; for I cannot redeem",["i","it."]],["div",{"id":"7","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.7","order":"02.09.004.20542"},["b","7"],"Now this",["i","was the manner"],"in former time in Israel concerning redeeming and concerning",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_7a"},"changing"],", for to confirm all things; a man plucked off his",["sup","b"],["a",{"href":"fn_7b"},"shoe"],", and gave",["i","it"],"to his neighbour: and this",["i","was"],"a testimony in Israel."],["div",{"id":"8","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.8","order":"02.09.004.20543"},["b","8"],"Therefore the kinsman said unto Boaz, Buy",["i","it"],"for thee. So he drew off his shoe."],["div",{"id":"9","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.9","order":"02.09.004.20544"},["b","9"],"¶And Boaz said unto the elders, and",["i","unto"],"all the people, Ye",["i","are"],"witnesses this day, that I have bought all that",["i","was"],"Elimelech’s, and all that",["i","was"],"Chilion’s and Mahlon’s, of the hand of Naomi."],["div",{"id":"10","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.10","order":"02.09.004.20545"},["b","10"],"Moreover Ruth the Moabitess, the wife of Mahlon, have I purchased to be my wife, to raise up the name of the dead upon his inheritance, that the",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_10a"},"name"],"of the dead be not cut off from among his brethren, and from the gate of his place: ye",["i","are"],"witnesses this day."],["div",{"id":"11","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.11","order":"02.09.004.20546"},["b","11"],"And all the people that",["i","were"],"in the gate, and the elders, said,",["i","We are"],"witnesses. The",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"make the woman that is come into thine house like Rachel and like Leah, which two did build the house of Israel: and",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_11a"},"do thou worthily"],"in Ephratah, and be famous in Beth-lehem:"],["div",{"id":"12","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.12","order":"02.09.004.20547"},["b","12"],"And let thy house be like the house of Pharez, whom Tamar bare unto Judah, of the seed which the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"shall give thee of this young woman."],["div",{"id":"13","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.13","order":"02.09.004.20548"},["b","13"],"¶So Boaz took Ruth, and she was his wife: and when he went in unto her, the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],"gave her conception, and she bare a son."],["div",{"id":"14","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.14","order":"02.09.004.20549"},["b","14"],"And the women said unto Naomi, Blessed",["i","be"],"the",["span.smallCaps","Lord"],", which hath not left thee this day without a kinsman, that his name may be famous in Israel."],["div",{"id":"15","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.15","order":"02.09.004.20550"},["b","15"],"And he shall be unto thee a restorer of",["i","thy"],"life, and a nourisher of thine",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_15a"},"old"],"age: for thy daughter in law, which loveth thee, which is better to thee than seven sons, hath born him."],["div",{"id":"16","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.16","order":"02.09.004.20551"},["b","16"],"And Naomi took the child, and laid it in her bosom, and became nurse unto it."],["div",{"id":"17","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.17","order":"02.09.004.20552"},["b","17"],"And the women her neighbours gave it a name, saying, There is a son born to Naomi; and they called his name Obed: he",["i","is"],"the father of Jesse, the father of David."],["div",{"id":"18","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.18","order":"02.09.004.20553"},["b","18"],"¶Now these",["i","are"],"the generations of",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_18a"},"Pharez"],": Pharez begat Hezron,"],["div",{"id":"19","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.19","order":"02.09.004.20554"},["b","19"],"And Hezron begat Ram, and Ram begat Amminadab,"],["div",{"id":"20","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.20","order":"02.09.004.20555"},["b","20"],"And Amminadab begat Nahshon, and Nahshon begat Salmon,"],["div",{"id":"21","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.21","order":"02.09.004.20556"},["b","21"],"And Salmon begat",["sup","a"],["a",{"href":"fn_21a"},"Boaz"],", and Boaz begat Obed,"],["div",{"id":"22","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.22","order":"02.09.004.20557"},["b","22"],"And Obed begat Jesse, and Jesse begat David."]]],"refs":[["div",{"id":"1a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.1a","order":"02.09.004.20558"},["b","1a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/23.10"},"Gen. 23:10"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/20.4"},"Josh. 20:4"],"."],["div",{"id":"1b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.1b","order":"02.09.004.20560"},["b","1b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/2.20"},"Ruth 2:20"],"."],["div",{"id":"1c","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.1c","order":"02.09.004.20562"},["b","1c"],"In Hebrew a manner of address to a certain unnamed person as “Mr. So & So.”"],["div",{"id":"2a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.2a","order":"02.09.004.20564"},["b","2a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/josh/20.4"},"Josh. 20:4"],"."],["div",{"id":"4a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.4a","order":"02.09.004.20566"},["b","4a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/lev/25.25"},"Lev. 25:25"],"."],["div",{"id":"4b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.4b","order":"02.09.004.20568"},["b","4b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/redemption"},"TG Redemption"],"."],["div",{"id":"5a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.5a","order":"02.09.004.20570"},["b","5a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/widows"},"TG Widows"],"."],["div",{"id":"5b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.5b","order":"02.09.004.20572"},["b","5b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/25.5.5-6"},"Deut. 25:5 (5–6)"],".",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/name"},"TG Name"],"."],["div",{"id":"6a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.6a","order":"02.09.004.20574"},["b","6a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/selfishness"},"TG Selfishness"],"."],["div",{"id":"6b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.6b","order":"02.09.004.20576"},["b","6b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/25.6.5-6"},"Deut. 25:6 (5–6)"],"."],["div",{"id":"7a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.7a","order":"02.09.004.20578"},["b","7a"],["span.small","OR"],"exchanging, doing business."],["div",{"id":"7b","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.7b","order":"02.09.004.20580"},["b","7b"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/25.9.5-10"},"Deut. 25:9 (5–10)"],"."],["div",{"id":"10a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.10a","order":"02.09.004.20582"},["b","10a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/deut/25.6"},"Deut. 25:6"],"."],["div",{"id":"11a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.11a","order":"02.09.004.20584"},["b","11a"],["span.small","OR"],"may you do well."],["div",{"id":"15a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.15a","order":"02.09.004.20586"},["b","15a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/tg/old-age"},"TG Old Age"],"."],["div",{"id":"18a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.18a","order":"02.09.004.20588"},["b","18a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/gen/38.29.1-30"},"Gen. 38:29 (1–30)"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/ot/1-chr/2.4.4-15"},"1 Chr. 2:4 (4–15)"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/1.3.3-6"},"Matt. 1:3 (3–6)"],";",["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/luke/3.33.23-38"},"Luke 3:33 (23–38)"],"."],["div",{"id":"21a","uri":"/scriptures/ot/ruth/4.21a","order":"02.09.004.20590"},["b","21a"],["a.scriptureRef",{"href":"/scriptures/nt/matt/1.5"},"Matt. 1:5"],"."]]}
